<section id="meaning" class="section paper">
  <h2>What 47 Means</h2>

  <p>
    The number 47 represents the relationship between structure and spirit.
    The 4 represents foundation, discipline, stability, and the work required
    to build something real. The 7 represents wisdom, intuition, inner vision,
    and spiritual awareness.
  </p>

  <p>
    Together, 47 represents building with purpose. It is not only a number,
    but a creative philosophy: stay grounded enough to create something solid,
    while staying spiritually aware enough to create something meaningful.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="chakras" class="section split">
  <div>
    <h2>The 4th Chakra</h2>
    <h3>Heart Center</h3>
    <p>
      In many yogic and tantric traditions, chakras are understood as subtle
      centers of energy used in meditation, breathwork, and spiritual practice.
      The 4th chakra is commonly associated with the heart center, compassion,
      balance, connection, and emotional truth.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h2>The 7th Chakra</h2>
    <h3>Crown Center</h3>
    <p>
      The 7th chakra is commonly associated with higher awareness, spiritual
      connection, contemplation, and the search for unity beyond the individual
      self. In symbolic terms, it represents the movement from personal effort
      toward higher understanding.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section paper">
  <h2>4 + 7 as a Creative Code</h2>

  <p>
    For RAK47, the 4 and 7 work together as a creative code. The 4 is the studio:
    the routine, the equipment, the engineering, the arrangement, and the craft.
    The 7 is the energy behind the work: instinct, inspiration, meaning, and the
    invisible feeling that makes music connect.
  </p>

  <p>
    This balance shapes the sound: raw but intentional, spiritual but grounded,
    edgy but professional.
  </p>
</section>

