<section class="section sources">
  <h2>Spiritual Context</h2>

  <p>
    Chakra means “wheel” and is used in Hindu and Tantric Buddhist traditions
    to describe subtle centers of psychic or spiritual energy. These concepts
    are part of religious and meditative systems, not modern anatomical science.
  </p>

  <p>
    This website uses the 4th and 7th chakras symbolically and respectfully:
    the heart as emotional truth and the crown as spiritual awareness.
  </p>
</section>

